vllm-shim local patch: fix mp_tuner.py mapping-error handler so the
tuner doesn't hang forever when mp.Pool silently replaces a crashed
worker.

When a worker dies (typically from a hipBLASLt kernel that faults
the GPU on a specific shape geometry), mp.Pool spawns a replacement
with a new PID. AITER's gpu_map was built once at pool startup, so
the new worker's PID isn't in it. The next task on that worker raises
KeyError(pid). Upstream's mapping_error branch appends to a never-read
dummy_failed_tasks list, doesn't record a dummy result, doesn't mark
the task completed, and doesn't trigger a pool restart, so the task
stays in remaining_tasks and re-raises KeyError on every polling
iteration. The tuner hangs.

This patch mirrors the accelerator_error branch immediately below:
record a dummy result, mark the task completed, and force a pool
restart so the existing restart path re-harvests PIDs and rebuilds
gpu_map. We lose two benchmark results per crash event (the worker
that died, and the task that hit the replacement worker) but the
tuner finishes; AITER's tuned-config writer picks the best surviving
kernel from the remaining ~1363 of 1365 candidates for the shape.

Upstream PR https://github.com/ROCm/aiter/pull/2309 proposed the same
fix in March 2026 and was closed without merging. PR #2662 (merged
April 9, 2026) fixed the parallel accelerator_error path but left
this branch stubbed out. Until upstream lands an equivalent fix, the
shim's Docker images carry this patch.

--- a/aiter/utility/mp_tuner.py
+++ b/aiter/utility/mp_tuner.py
@@ -472,10 +472,24 @@
                 error_type = type(e).__name__
                 is_mapping_error = _is_mapping_error(e)
                 is_accelerator_error = _is_accelerator_error(e)
-                # not restart as this is not root use
-                if is_mapping_error:
-                    error_msg = f"[Mapping Error] Task {k} - Process PID not in GPU map: {error_type} - {e}"
-                    dummy_failed_tasks.append((k, "mapping error"))
+                # vllm-shim patch: treat mapping_error like accelerator_error.
+                # mp.Pool silently spawned a replacement worker after a crash,
+                # so GPUIDMap doesn't know the new PID. Without this fix the
+                # task stays in remaining_tasks forever, re-raising KeyError
+                # on every loop iteration. Upstream PR #2309 proposed the
+                # same fix in March 2026 and was closed without merging.
+                if is_mapping_error:
+                    error_msg = f"[Mapping Error] Task {k} - Process PID not in GPU map: {error_type} - {e}"
+                    print(error_msg, flush=True)
+                    failed_tasks.append((k, "mapping error"))
+                    dummy_results = []
+                    add_dummy_result(k, dummy_results)
+                    result_dict[k] = (
+                        dummy_results if shape_grouped else [dummy_results[0]]
+                    )
+                    completed_this_round.append((k, async_result))
+                    pool_restart_needed = True
+                    break
                 elif is_accelerator_error:
                     # GPU fault (e.g. illegal memory access): worker returns exception instead of
                     # hanging. Unlike hang->timeout, the faulting worker may stay alive and accept
